      "side": 0,
      "message": "It does it in a different place, but yes, it does something similar (and for the same reason).\n\nDWrite\u0027s formula is:\n  multiplier \u003d fgLightness \u003e 0.75 ? 0.0 :\n               fgLightness \u003e 0.50 ? 4.0 - (0.75 - fgLightness) // lerp between [0,1]\n                                  : 1.0;\n  adjustedContrast \u003d contrast * multiplier;\n\n(FWIW, fgLightness doesn\u0027t appear to have been gamma-corrected in DWrite; it\u0027s doing the \"standard\" RGB -\u003e grey conversion... 0.3*r + 0.59*g + 0.11*b)\n\nSo DWrite is applying the full contrast enhancment until text lightness gets to 0.5, where it starts to taper off, and applies no enhancement at 0.75 lightness.",
      "parentUuid": "eceb1309_81a9bae9",
      "revId": "f7cce2b243b2f44c2e37036d3280d26a398e1207",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
